==English==
[[Category:Vulgarities]]
===Alternative spellings===
*[[fuck-up]] ''(UK, noun)''
*[[fuckup]] ''(US regional, noun)'' 

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[fuck]] [[up]]}}

# One who can never seem to get anything quite right; one who errs frequently.
#:''He is such a '''fuck up''' it's not funny.''

===Verb===
{{en-verb|fucks up|fucking up|fucked up}}

# ''(intransitive)'' {{slang}} To make a mistake, to go wrong
#:''You really '''fucked up''' this time.''
# ''(transitive)'' To [[botch]] or make a mess of
#:''I '''fucked up''' question 3 of the exam.''
# ''(transitive)'' to [[injure]] or [[damage]]
#:''You come one step nearer, I'm going to '''fuck''' you '''up''' good.''